\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Sensitivity of the logit-based temperature curves to the missing-digit imputation rule. We compare the default rule, which assigns every missing digit the minimum returned top-20 log-probability, against a zero-mass alternative. The plotted quantities are the absolute differences in the resulting \(S(T)\) and \(R(T)\) curves. Across all five models and all plotted temperatures, the discrepancies remain very small.}}{17}{figure.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:logprob-imputation-sensitivity}{{9}{17}{Sensitivity of the logit-based temperature curves to the missing-digit imputation rule. We compare the default rule, which assigns every missing digit the minimum returned top-20 log-probability, against a zero-mass alternative. The plotted quantities are the absolute differences in the resulting \(S(T)\) and \(R(T)\) curves. Across all five models and all plotted temperatures, the discrepancies remain very small}{figure.9}{}}
